  "active_lock_reason": null,
  "body": "### Description:\r\nWhen a node receives a blob sidecar via `by_root` and `by_range` requests, we currently validate the alignment of the blob sidecar's commitment, blobs, and proof fields. However, several crucial validations are absent:\r\n\r\n### Missing Validations:\r\n1. Ensure the block root corresponds with the associated block.\r\n2. Validate that the parent root aligns with the block's parent root.\r\n3. Check that the proposer index is consistent with the block.\r\n4. Confirm the slot is in sync with the block.\r\n\r\n### Concern:\r\nThe absence of these validations can make it feasible for a peer to forward a spurious blob sidecar to our node, even if the commitments, blobs, and proofs appear legitimate.",
